  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering at national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. United States:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n\n3. European Union:\n- Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Comprehensive regulations for financial institutions\n- Enhanced customer due diligence requirements\n\n4. Key Regulatory Measures:\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Financial institution monitoring\n- Asset seizure and criminal prosecution\n\n5. Implementation Strategies:\n- Mandatory reporting of large cash transactions\n- Background checks on financial transactions\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n- Penalties for non-compliance\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds and integrating them into the legitimate financial system.",
